SIMPLE: peg
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peg
<hw>Peg</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧g)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>pegge</ets>; cf. Sw. <ets>pigg</ets>, Dan. <ets>pig</ets> a point,
prickle, and E. <ets>peak</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small,
pointed piece of wood, used in fastening boards together, in attaching
the soles of boots or shoes, etc.; <as>as, a shoe
<ex>peg</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A wooden pin, or nail, on which to hang things, as
coats, etc. Hence, colloquially and figuratively: A support; a reason; a
pretext; <as>as, a <ex>peg</ex> to hang a claim upon</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>One of the pins of a musical instrument, on which
the strings are strained.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>One of the pins used for marking points on a
cribbage board.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A step; a degree; esp. in the slang phrase ⟦ldquo⟧To
take one down a <xex>peg</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To screw papal authority to the highest <qex>peg</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And took your grandees down a <qex>peg</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Hudibras.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>A drink of spirits, usually whisky or brandy diluted
with soda water.</def> <mark>[India]</mark></p>

<p><q>This over, the club will be visited for a
⟦ldquo⟧<qex>peg</qex>,⟦rdquo⟧ Anglice drink.</q> <rj><qau>Harper's
Mag.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <fld>(Baseball)</fld> <def>a hard throw, especially one
made to put out a baserunner; <as>as, the <ex>peg</ex> to the plate went
wild</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>peg board</b></col>, <cd>a board with multiple small
holes into which pegs can be inserted in different arrays so as to form
hooks from which to hang tools or other objects for convenient access;
it is typically hung from a wall in a workshop.</cd> -- <col><b>Peg
ladder</b></col>, <cd>a ladder with but one standard, into which cross
pieces are inserted.</cd> -- <col><b>Peg tankard</b></col>, <cd>an
ancient tankard marked with pegs, so as divide the liquor into equal
portions.</cd> ⟦ldquo⟧Drink down to your <xex>peg</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Longfellow.</au> -- <col><b>Peg tooth</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Fleam
tooth</cref> under <er>Fleam</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Peg top</b></col>,
<cd>a boy's top which is spun by throwing it.</cd> -- <col><b>Screw
peg</b></col>, <cd>a small screw without a head, for fastening
soles.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peg</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Peg
<hw>Peg</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧g)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Pegged</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Pegging</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To put pegs into; to fasten the parts of with pegs; <as>as, to
<ex>peg</ex> shoes</as>; to confine with pegs; to restrict or limit
closely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will rend an oak⟦br⟧
And <qex>peg</qex> thee in his knotty entrails.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Cribbage)</fld> <def>To score with a peg, as points
in the game; <as>as, she <ex>pegged</ex> twelve points</as>.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To identify; to recognize; <as>as, she
<ex>pegged</ex> him as a good carpenter; he was <ex>pegged</ex> as a
blowhard as soon as he started speaking; he was <ex>pegged</ex> as a
exceptional player even in high school</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Baseball)</fld> <def>To throw (a ball); <as>as, he
<ex>pegged</ex> the runner out at second</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peg</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Peg
<hw>Peg</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To work diligently, as one who pegs
shoes; -- usually with <xex>on</xex>, <xex>at</xex>, or <xex>away</xex>;
<as>as, to <ex>peg</ex> away at a task</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pegador</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
